        &lt;help&gt;&lt;![CDATA[&lt;h4&gt;A quick word&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It looks like this might be the first time you are running &lt;strong&gt;SnippetNow&lt;/strong&gt;. If this is the case, here&amp;#39;s a couple of suggestions to get you started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The function of this page is to keep track of useful &lt;em&gt;snippets&lt;/em&gt; that you may want to have for future reference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;To get started&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There&amp;#39;s a couple of way you can go about this, but my suggestion would be to create at least 1 &lt;strong&gt;APPLICATION&lt;/strong&gt; and 1 &lt;strong&gt;TYPE&lt;/strong&gt; first. The idea behind this is that when you are creating &lt;em&gt;snippets&lt;/em&gt; you want as much meta data available to filter and find those snippets you want to reference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;APPLICATION&lt;/strong&gt;: Service Portal&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TYPE&lt;/strong&gt;: Widget - Client Script&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then go hog wild and add those snippets!&lt;/p&gt;
